895static void kinsim_emxEnsureCapacity_real_T(emxArray_real_T_kinsim_2link__T



896  *emxArray, int32_T oldNumel)



897{



898  int32_T newNumel;



899  int32_T i;



900  void *newData;



901  if (oldNumel < 0) {



902    oldNumel = 0;



903  }



904



905  newNumel = 1;



906  for (i = 0; i < emxArray->numDimensions; i++) {



907    newNumel *= emxArray->size[i];



908  }



909



910  if (newNumel > emxArray->allocatedSize) {



911    i = emxArray->allocatedSize;



912    if (i < 16) {



913      i = 16;



914    }



915



916    while (i < newNumel) {



917      if (i > 1073741823) {



918        i = MAX_int32_T;



919      } else {



920        i <<= 1;



921      }



922    }



923



924    newData = calloc(static_cast<uint32_T>(i), sizeof(real_T));



925    if (emxArray->data != NULL) {



926      memcpy(newData, emxArray->data, sizeof(real_T) * oldNumel);



927      if (emxArray->canFreeData) {



928        free(emxArray->data);



929      }



930    }



931



932    emxArray->data = (real_T *)newData;



933    emxArray->allocatedSize = i;



934    emxArray->canFreeData = true;



935  }



936}
